Deputy President Rigathi Gachagua has reiterated that the Kenya Kwanza administration strives to work with all leaders regardless of their political affiliation. The DP said the government is committed to including every part of the country in its development agenda. He spoke on Monday at the Harambee House Annex when he hosted leaders from Kisii and Nyamira Counties for consultations on the regions' development agenda. They included Education CS Ezekiel Machogu, National Assembly Majority Whip Sylvanus Osoro and MPs Innocent Obiri (Bobasi), Steve Mogaka (West Mugirango), Patrick Osero (Borabu), Charles Onchoke (Bonchari), Daniel Manduku (Nyaribari Masaba). Others were Anthony Kibagendi (Kitutu Chache South), Jerusha Momanyi (Woman Rep Nyamira County), Doris Donya (Woman Rep Kisii County), Alfa Miruka (Bomachoge Chache), Japhet Nyakundi (Kitutu Chache North), Joash Nyamoko (North Mugirango) Essy Okenyuri (Nominated Senator) and Gloria Orwoba (Nominated Senator). Gachagua said the government was keen on ensuring equitable development, promising the leaders its commitment to ensuring the region gets a deserving share of national resources. "President William Ruto has opened the door for those ready to work with his administration because his sole interest is to ensure development in every part of the country," he said. The leaders pledged their support for the Kenya Kwanza administration,Â  saying different political associations will not stop them from working with the government.